This paper deals with the issue of balancing data privacy for individuals with societal priorities such as counterterrorism and disease containment. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Computer Science and Cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper introduces a computational model for identifying and taking action upon members of a targeted subpopulation while minimizing the compromise of privacy for the protected. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Systems and Control (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the use of graph search methods and the injection of noise to ensure privacy for the protected, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
